column5: Was an awsome fun weekend for us, hope everyones was aswell. Heres some pics to share, enjoy !
Excellent, looks like you had a great time by the campfire.  Nice fish
Sounds like a great weekend.  I wish I had a fire keeping me warm on the creek Sat morning at 4:00am in the rain...
Very nice Way to open a season!

Thanks guys, the fire was an absolout must for sat mourning. By 4 am everything around us was soaked, good thing we had the fire going all night so it had really hot embers that dried the wet wood up nicely. I must say this opener was one of my better ones from past years, I just hope others can also say so.
Some real nice bigguns there. Looks like you had a great opener/trout season. amazing pics too!
Love the quality of the photo's, great catches!! Some real nice size Rainbow's there.   Thanks for taking the time to post,  MTBF
just upping my post count.... nothing to see here...  G
Great pictures thanks for putting them up.
sweet man.  it's a great time of year!
great times indeed! minus the crazy rain from 2am-6am LOL!
Great pics bud, what a morning that was. Loosing count of fish is one thing, but loosing count of triple headers is a whole different ball game
Ahhh good good times indeed! The fish are definatly of bigger size this year, exactly what i was expecting after seeing the salmon and bows of the fall run.
